author: Will Anderson
title: Australian golf trip turns tragic for Austin executives killed in plane crash
text: Enlarge Russell Munsch, founding partner of law firm Munsch Hardt Kopf & Harr PC, is reportedly… more The five people killed when a plane crashed Tuesday into a mall in Australia included at least three Austin-area residents, including a partner at a law firm and a technology executive. Media reports and social media posts identified the deceased as Russell Munsch of Austin, founding partner of Munsch Hardt Kopf & Harr PC; Glenn Garland , former CEO of Austin-based CLEAResult Consulting , an energy efficiency consulting firm; and Greg DeHaven of Spicewood, a professional golfer. Russell Munsch, founding partner of law firm Munsch Hardt Kopf & Harr PC, is reportedly… more The pilot also died. The other passenger has not been identified. The aircraft was headed from Melbourne to King Island, about 150 miles offshore near Tasmania, for a golfing trip, according to the Austin American-Statesman . But the pilot reported a "catastrophic engine failure" shortly after takeoff and the plane crashed into an outlet mall near the airport. Will Anderson coordinates digital coverage of business news.
